<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-27T13:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-27T13:49:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1219.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-27T14:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1915—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>French Legation threatened and a forcible entry attempted for the purpose
                            of taking out the President. French Minister and British Chargé
                            d’Affaires have telegraphed for ships. Situation very grave and the
                            presence of war vessels as soon as possible necessary.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>